snippet.textDisplay: This composition has everything except the soul.. over mixed, over-experimented in a desperate bid to make it “palatable”, marketable to wider audiences.. no disrespect to the artists, they’re all very talented.. however, it still doesn’t hit the way it’s supposed to..for example, the misplaced rock-reggae treatment/groove (with heavy bass and drums replacing Assamese percussion and instruments) fundamentally disrupts the core aesthetic of a Bihu/ Assamese folk song  (and there are lakhs of such gems).. this wasn’t the case with Papon’s Jhumoor
snippet.textOriginal: This composition has everything except the soul.. over mixed, over-experimented in a desperate bid to make it “palatable”, marketable to wider audiences.. no disrespect to the artists, they’re all very talented.. however, it still doesn’t hit the way it’s supposed to..for example, the misplaced rock-reggae treatment/groove (with heavy bass and drums replacing Assamese percussion and instruments) fundamentally disrupts the core aesthetic of a Bihu/ Assamese folk song  (and there are lakhs of such gems).. this wasn’t the case with Papon’s Jhumoor
